            <div type="translation">
                <p>Brothers, I urge you, as foreigners and exiles, to abstain from sinful desires.
</p>
            </div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>Lines 1-5 do not survive. The inscription is from Peter's Epistle I, 2:11: Ἀγαπητοί, παρακαλῶ ὡς παροίκους καὶ παρεπιδήμους ἀπέχεσθαι τῶν σαρκικῶν ἐπιθυμιῶν. However, the incipit Ἀδελφοί, παρακαλῶ ὑμᾶς, originates from Paul's epistles. Text reconstruction was based on the example of Apostle Peter's mural <ref target="MedCY.055.013.html">(MedCY.055.013)</ref> from the church of the Transfiguration of the Saviour at Sotera.

</p>
